   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER FIVE THE BUILDING UP OF THE BODY OF CHRIST</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>BY THE TRANSFORMATION IN LIFE 1 Scripture Reading: John 3:5-6; 2 Cor 3:18; Rom 12:2a; 8:30c; Heb 2:10a; Titus 3:5b OUTLINE The complete salvation of God: Sanctification in God's calling 1 Pet 1:2b.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The redemption of Christ Rom 3:24b.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Washing of our sins by the blood of Christ Rev 1:5b; 1 Pet 1:2c; 1 John 1:7.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Forgiveness of sins Acts 2:38.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Objective justification by God Rom 3:24a.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Reconciliation to God Rom 5:10a.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Objective sanctification by the blood of Christ Heb 10:29b.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Regeneration by the Spirit Titus 3:5b.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Full salvation of God Acts 16:31.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Daily salvation in the life of Christ Rom 5:10; 1 Pet 2:2.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Washing by the Spirit 1 Cor 6:11a.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Anointing of the Spirit 1 John 2:20, 27.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Subjective sanctification in the Spirit 1 Cor 6:11b; Rom 15:16b; 6:19b, 22b.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Subjective justification in the Spirit 1 Cor 6:11c.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>God abiding in us 1 John 3:24; 4:13.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Christ making His home in our hearts Eph 3:17.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The renewing of the Holy Spirit Titus 3:5c; Eph 4:23; Rom 12:2a.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Transformation from the Lord Spirit 2 Cor 3:18b; Rom 12:2b.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>Conformation to the image of the Lord Rom 8:29a.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Redemption of the body Rom 8:23b; Eph 1:14b; 4:30b.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Glorification in the glory of God Rom 8:30c; Heb 2:10; 1 Pet 5:10.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>The vital importance of transformation in the complete salvation of God: Of the twenty-one aspects listed above, regeneration, transformation, and glorification are the three vital aspects in God's complete salvation: Regeneration brings the divine life into the believers to germinate and generate their spirit John 3:5-6.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Transformation carries the divine essence into all the components of the believers' soul mind, emotion, and will to transform them metabolically 2 Cor 3:18; Rom 12:2a.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Glorification saturates the believers' body with the glory of God to glorify them by bringing them into God's glory Rom 8:30c; Heb 2:10a.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Regeneration transpires in the believers' spirit at the moment when they receive Christ as their Redeemer, Savior, and life once for all; transformation is taking place in the believers' soul for their entire Christian life until they will be transfigured and glorified in their body; and glorification will be consummated at the Lord's rapture once for all when He comes to meet them.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>All three aspects are organic and by these three steps the believers' entire being spirit, soul, and body will be organically mingled with the processed and consummated Triune God.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>The significance of transformation: Not merely an outward change.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>An inward transformation in nature and essence.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>The move of the divine life in the believers' inner being.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>The positive organic reaction of the divine life in the believers' entire being.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>The metabolic constitution in the believers' renewed being.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>The expression of the divine image's attributes in the believers' renewed being to be the virtues of the believers' new man.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>The manifestation of the processed and consummated Triune God in the believers' new man.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>The masterpiece of the consummated Spirit of the Triune God as the Lord Spirit throughout the believers' entire being as the new creation by His renewing work 2 Cor 3:18b; Titus 3:5b.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>Accomplished in the believers who, with unveiled face, behold and reflect as a mirror the glory of the Lord 2 Cor 3:18a.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>Issuing in the glorious image of the glorified Lord from one degree of His glory to another until the believers enter into His glory to be glorified by the bright splendor of God's glory 2 Cor 3:18b; Heb 2:10a; Rom 8:30c.</S>
   </TEXT>
